Note from the Chairman















"Trust” Is Part of Our Name for a Reason
We cannot think of a better word to define us. It hearkens back to an earlier era, when each customer’s legacy was attended and protected with the utmost care. Our traditional view of customer service is what sets us apart – and, ultimately, what keeps families with us for generations.
An Uncommon Degree of Service
Smithfield Trust customers can expect much more from us than a typical, larger firm. We know each and every one of them by name, and we give them direct access to any member of our team at any time.
Our investment advisors continually monitor the day-to-day developments that affect our customers’ accounts, a fact that is reflected in our personalized monthly letter.
No Conflicts of Interest
Smithfield Trust is a fee-based company, which means we are not motivated by commissions and therefore are always working in our customers’ best interests. We do not own any funds, nor do we offer mutual funds because of the additional fees involved.


